Confederation of African Football (CAF) President, Patrice Motsepe has given his verdict on Nigeria’s Africa Cup of Nations (AFCON) 2021 tie with Tunisia. Motsepe described Nigeria’s AFCON 2021 clash with Tunisia as a ‘big game’, adding that he will be at the stadium, Garoua to watch the tie. He also expressed confidence that whichever proceeds between Nigeria and Tunisia will make CAF very proud. Nigeria will face Tunisia in the AFCON 2021 Round of 16 tie on Sunday night at the Roumde Adija stadium in Cameroon. Speaking to Mosaique FM on Saturday, Motsepe said: “Big game, I will be there. “Two nations with a proud football history and I’m confident that whichever proceeds will make us very proud.” The kick-off time for the Nigeria vs Tunisia game is 8 pm.